#  Load & Dataframe 
from sklearn import datasets
import pandas as pd

iris = datasets.load_iris()
y = pd.DataFrame(iris.target)
y.columns=['labels']
data = pd.DataFrame(iris.data)
data.columns=['Sepal length','Sepal width','Petal length','Petal width']
data = pd.concat([data,y],axis=1)
